[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Stage 2: Expert Discussion
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conflicts and overlaps:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 1. **N1 (Comprehend Medical VPC endpoint) reinforces S1 (IAM scoping):** Both findings relate to the separation between Comprehend and Comprehend Medical as distinct services. The IAM permissions list them as separate actions (`comprehend:DetectSentiment` vs. `comprehendmedical:DetectPHI`), which is correct. But the VPC section treats them as one. Fixing N1 reinforces the mental model that these are separate services with separate access patterns.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 2. **A1 (endpoint hosting cost) is independent of other findings** but the most impactful for reader trust. A decision-maker who reads "$550/month" and gets a $910/month bill has a trust problem with the cookbook. This is the same class of issue found in Recipe 8.1 and should be a standard checklist item.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 3. **A2 (missing DLQ) and S3 (EventBridge PHI leakage)** are both about what happens when the pipeline encounters edge cases. A2 handles technical failures; S3 handles data leakage in the success path. Both are about defensive patterns the recipe should encourage.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 4. **N2 (EventBridge no VPC endpoint) is a real deployment issue** that contradicts the recipe's stated VPC architecture. If all Lambdas are in VPC with only VPC endpoints (no NAT), the EventBridge call in Step 4 will silently fail or timeout. This needs either an architectural change (use SNS instead) or a clear note about NAT Gateway requirement for alerting.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Priority resolution:** A1 (cost) and N1 (VPC endpoint) are the highest priority because they cause deployment failures or budget surprises. S1 (IAM scoping) is next as a compliance gap. A2 (DLQ) and N2 (EventBridge connectivity) are architectural completeness issues.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
